Jungle Book is a collection of stories by Rudyard Kipling, set in the Indian jungle. The main character is Mowgli, a boy who was raised by wolves and lives among the animals. He learns the laws of the jungle from his friends Baloo the bear, Bagheera the panther, and Kaa the python. He also faces many dangers, such as the man-eating tiger Shere Khan, the mischievous monkeys, and the greedy humans. Along the way, he discovers his true identity and his place in the world.
